Source: Sheep.  Part 1, Sheep husbandry
Author: STEVENS
Vol / Page: 59
Edition:
Quote: During the last thirty years two methods of grazing management have been adopted. The first and oldest is 'set-stocking.' In some areas cattle will be carried as a floating grazing unit or 'set-stocked' to deal with surplus growth.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1958
Source: Sheep.  Part 1, Sheep husbandry
Author: STEVENS
Vol / Page: 61
Edition:
Quote: Set-stocking allowed the ewes to become too fat at times of the year.. The most satisfactory solution appears to be a compromise between the two systems, using set-stocking from lambing to weaning, and controlled rotational grazing during the summer, autumn and winter.
Notes:

